To further confirm the enhanced photocatalytic activity of C-dots modified g-C3N4, photocatalytic hydrogen production was also performed under visible irradiation. It can be seen that the hydrogen evolution rate sharply increased from 91 (S0 sample) to 218umolg−1
                        h−1 (S5 sample), increased by a factor of about 2.4 times (Fig. 8
                        ).
